g.text: The flow represents the retrieval of published Blocking Condition at the Gateway server start-up to update the Throttle Data Holder.The flow starts activating Blocking Condition Retriever to query all published active Blocking Conditions from the Key Manager component to update the Throttle Data Holder map.

g.desc: The flow represents the Blocking Condition publishing flow in...
g.text: The flow represents the Blocking Condition publishing flow in WSO2 API Manager server.The flow starts from creating and publishing a Blocking Condition from the Admin portal up-to the update process on Throttle Data Holder in Gateway.

g.text: The flow represents validation of the Blocking Conditions during the API invocation.The Throttle Handler in the Gateway pulls the data from the Throttle Data Holder to verify the conditions during the runtime.
